      "options": "<div style=\"padding:8px 0 4px;line-height:1.55;\"><p><strong>How each rule is used.</strong></p><p><strong>Tariff Number</strong>: optional exact HS/customs code match.<br><strong>Custom Material</strong>: matches Item Custom Material from the article workbook's <code>DOUANE MATERIAL</code> column.<br><strong>Value Per Kg</strong>: declared customs value per kg.<br><strong>Rate Percent</strong>: customs percent applied to the declared customs value.<br><strong>Sequence</strong>: tie-breaker when multiple matching rules exist. Lower sequence wins.</p><p><strong>Formula</strong><br><code>Customs Fee = Value Per Kg x Total Kg x Rate Percent / 100</code></p><p><strong>Example</strong><br>Custom Material <code>ACIER</code>, Value Per Kg <code>13</code>, Total Weight <code>100 kg</code>, Rate Percent <code>25</code><br><code>Customs Fee = 13 x 100 x 25% = 325</code></p></div>"
